narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Overview of some of the basic theories that shaped different movements in the history of art, some discussion of how it applies to your own work.
Download the syllabus, do the readings, and don't take the course. Waste of 2 hours every week.
Yes, as long as you have some interest in the topics.
A good introduction to modern art history and theory. The instructor is wonderful and leads good discussions. Would recommend!
Yes but only if you have a previous engagement or serious interest in "art theory."
This class was a great way to study contemporary art history. I highly recommend it, especially for art majors or others with an interest in the subject. The instructor is great.
